{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"9316ff30-4f64-43f4-a4fa-6a08bd92f082","content":"Your project already has the HotReload extension. To use it, run:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --hotreload\n```\n\nThis starts the test runner in **watch mode**. It will:\n\n1. **Run all tests** initially\n2. **Watch for file changes** — when you save edits to your test or source files, it automatically **re-runs affected tests** without a full rebuild\n\nThis is much faster than repeatedly running `dotnet test` because it uses hot-reload to patch the running process in-place.\n\n**Workflow:**\n1. Start `dotnet test --hotreload` in one terminal\n2. Open `EmailValidatorTests.cs` (or the code under test) in your editor\n3. Make a fix, save → tests re-run automatically\n4. Repeat until green ✅\n\nPress `Ctrl+C` to stop when you're done.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"be8f1520-a979-4c7a-b670-b8d0318198c2","outputTokens":202},"id":"9305d908-6bb1-43f8-ac14-7e45df95834b","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:43:38.503Z","parentId":"7039c8cb-a564-40d8-b63d-4c057e2d7f08"}
